Thank you for your interest in our internship opening. As a next Assignmentstep, we are expecting you to complete a short assignment and submit to hello@shunyeka.com.

You have to complete the assignment that you are comfortable with. If you complete both assignment and explain in assignment induction round, then you will not require 2nd technical round.

Assignment 1: 
- Create a sample "Hello World" application using the following.
  https://pythonspot.com/flask-hello-world/
- Store the code on github in a public repository.
- Create a docker image to run the application.
- Use AWS CodePipeline to build docker image by fetching latest code from github and store it in the ECR or dockerhub.
- Deploy the application docker image on AWS ECS using Fargate
- Create all the required components i.e. ALB etc to make the application publically accessible.

- ADDITIONAL POINTS: create cloud formation Or terraform template to deploy application in aws

Note: You need to sign up to AWS account for this assignment. Given assignment cloud resources are included in AWS free tire usage. For any clarification for AWS billing reach out to yogini@shunyeka.com. Cost of running the above assignment (if any) will be borne by the company 
Make sure to run the resources only when required like ALB etc and use free tier services wherever possible.

Assignment 2: Jira Task Application

- Create a Jira account https://www.atlassian.com/software/jira/free
- Create a Jira Project https://support.atlassian.com/jira-software-cloud/docs/create-a-new-project/
- Develop a Python flask/django application to do the following.
	- A UI Form to submit the following details.
		- Title, Description, Jira Project ID
	- Connect to Jira using Jira Python SDK  https://jira.readthedocs.io/installation.html
	- Check if Jira task exists with the same title. If not create a new task, if already exists, send error message that a task with same title already exists.
	- Create a Jira task using the above details provided by the use.
	- Store the details in MongoDB database. (https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas/register)